Context: The George Brown College is involved in research on managing renewable energy. They have successfully completed projects related to harnessing wind and solar energy. The college focuses on productive economies and innovation by collaborating with industry and community partners. The Food Innovation Research Centre (FIRSt) at the college helps get new food products and services into market and onto store shelves. For more information, you can contact them via phone at 416-415-2000 or TTY: 1-877-515-5559, email ask.george@georgebrown.ca, or sign up for updates on their website. The college has a land acknowledgment and offers various programs with application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, and tours available for signing up to be informed about. Their website contains information that is subject to change without notice.
